parameters:
Ever since the bandits came, I haven't been feeling well...
It's really quite troublesome...

Thanks to you, the peace of this village has been preserved.
My health has returned as well... I'm truly grateful.
Oh? Aren't you... from that dango shop in Edo...?

Hello. I was a bit curious, so I came to see what the
village looks like... Where is the bandit gang?

Ah, beyond the wooden gate at the top left of the village is
the bandit gang's territory. There's an old castle from the
Warring States period there, and a man named Kousaka Jinrai
has made it his lair as the bandit leader, strutting around
like he owns the place.

Thank you for telling meâ™ª I'll go and take a look at what
the bandits are up to.

What?! That's too reckless! There are many bandits. It's
dangerous for a girl to go alone! It would be better to wait
for someone from the magistrate's office to come...

It's alright. The bandit leader is a man named Kousaka,
right? I'll go and settle things with him. See you!
~~~~!? (Is she really going to be okay?)

Those bandits have made the old castle their stronghold. But
are you really going to be okay on your own?

...I heard from the villagers that a girl resembling Mouse
Komachi defeated the bandits... Could it be... you...?

No, no! That's not me!? I'm not Mouse Komachi! It's just a
case of mistaken identity! Ahaha...!

Village Chief of Shintai Village, it's been a while. Um...
thank you for the other day.

No, no, not at all. This village was saved by you. It was
only natural to ask the magistrate for a pardon. Seeing you
out and about, you've been cleared of all charges, haven't
you? I'm glad I realized you were the thief Mouse Komachi
and petitioned the authorities on your behalf.

No... I was spared the death penalty, but I was exiled to a
distant island... and then I just came back on my own...
ahaha...

--Eh?! You escaped from the island? My, my, that's so like
the master thief Mouse Komachi. The term 'carefree' must
have been coined for someone like you.
Ehehe, I'll take that as a complimentâ™ª

I haven't properly thanked you yet for driving out the band
of thieves. This is some wild boar meat caught in the
village. Please accept it.
Wow! So much?! Thank you very much, Village Chief!

--Received 20 pieces of [Color_17]ã€Wild Boar Meatã€‘\c[17]
from the Village Chief!

The bandits are gone, and the villagers are happy too. I
want to thank you on behalf of the village. Thank you so
much.
